                            <comment id="14755813" author="rsunderbabu" created="Mon, 24 Feb 2025 07:01:59 -0800"  >All 3 tests are making sure that epsilon GC handles various OOM scenarios as expected.&lt;br/&gt;
1. Memory exhaustion with no extra flags&lt;br/&gt;
2. Memory exhaustion with heap dump&lt;br/&gt;
3. Memory exhaustion with error handler&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
In all 3 cases, the tests can honour any extra flags passed to the test.&lt;br/&gt;
The tests shouldn&amp;#39;t be run for other GCs and that is taken care by &amp;quot;@requires&amp;quot; field.&lt;br/&gt;
Hence, the tests don&amp;#39;t need vm.flagless property. Instead, the flags passed to the test externally should be applied to the spawned processes.</comment>
